<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - DISASSEMBLE -
        WHEEL DIFFERENTIAL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>WHEEL DIFFERENTIAL</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>During following procedure, place differential assembly on a soft surface to prevent damage when
                    ring gear falls off its mounting position.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove nuts and bolts that fasten the ring gear to the differential cases. The ring gear
                will fall free. If the ring gear does not fall, tap the outer diameter with soft mallet to loosen.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Punch mark differential cases for correct location during assembly. Remove bolts and lift
                off plain differential case half (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401215">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401215" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401215" filename="../figg14/g1401215.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Punch Mark Differential Cases</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove side gear and thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove spider, side pinions and thrust washers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove side gear and thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing cone from plain case half in two steps (refer to the Note on the next
                page):
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">FIRST, mount splitter vertically to split bearing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401216">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401216" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401216" filename="../figg14/g1401216.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Mount Splitter Vertically to Split Bearing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">SECOND, mount splitter horizontally to remove cone (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401217">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401217" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401217" filename="../figg14/g1401217.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Mount Splitter Horizontally to Remove Cone</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Because of the differential case design variance, the first step in removing bearing cone
                            can be omitted for axle models 15040, 19050, and 19055.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing cone from flanged case half using suitable puller (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401218">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401218" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401218" filename="../figg14/g1401218.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Bearing Cone</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean and inspect parts for damage or wear. Replace as required.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
